-- Vestas Winds Systems Wins Turbine Orders From Italian Project Developers
-- Louise Downing
-- 2010-07-12T14:27:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-12/vestas-winds-systems-wins-turbine-orders-from-italian-project-developers.html

          
          
                  July 12 (Bloomberg New Energy Finance) --  Vestas Wind
Systems A/S , the world’s largest maker of wind turbines,
received an order from project developers Volturino Wind and CO-
VER Industrial for 13 of its 1.8-megawatt machines.  
 Under the contract, Vestas will be responsible for supply,
installation and commissioning of the turbines and a five-year
service agreement, according to the company’s website.  
 Delivery of the turbines is scheduled to start in the first
half of 2011 and the project will be completed by the end of the
year. The 23-megawatt wind farm will be in Apulia, Italy.  
 The wind farm will generate about 78,000 megawatt hours of
clean power per year at a capacity factor of 38 percent.  
 Volturino Wind is a project company of BKW Italia,
controlled by the Swiss utility BKW FMB Energy AG.  
